hh3cDot11STATION.name: hh3cDot11STATION

revisions.description: Add new node hh3cDot11StationUpTimeTicks, hh3cDot11StationSecIEStatus to hh3cDot11StationAssociateTable.
Add new node hh3cDot11StaRxErrDataFrameCnt and hh3cDot11StaTxRetryDataFrameCnt to hh3cDot11StationStatisTable
Modified to add new trap and add hh3cDot11StationRxNoise to hh3cDot11StationAssociateTable.
The initial revision of this MIB module.

hh3cDot11STATION.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip: 100085
hh3cDot11STATION.description: This MIB defines the configuration and statistic information of stations. GLOSSARY IEEE 802.11 Standard to encourage interoperability among wireless networking equipment. Access point (AP) Transmitter/receiver (transceiver) device that commonly connects and transports data between a wireless network and a wired network. Access control (AC) To control and manage multi-APs, it will bridge wireless and wired network. Control And Provisioning of Wireless Access Points Protocol The short name of protocol is CAPWAP. AC will control and manage AP by CAPWAP tunnel protocol defined by IETF. Also, a data tunnel will be set up between AC and AP. BSS IEEE 802.11 Basic Service Set (Radio Cell). The BSS of an AP comprises of the stations directly associated with the AP. station (Client Station) A wireless device in a wireless network associated with an access point. MIC Message Integrity Check. A MIC can, optionally, be added to WEP-encrypted 802.11 frames. SSID Radio Service Set ID. It is used for identification during association. STA (WSTA) A non-AP 802.11 wireless station. WEP Wired Equivalent Privacy. 'WEP' is generally used to refer to 802.11 encryption. RSSI It is the received signal strength indication. It suggests the quality of received signal. RTS Request to Send, it is used to gain control of the medium for the transmission of 'large' frames, in which 'large' is defined by the RTS threshold in the network card driver. CTS Clear to Send, it is used to answer RTS frames. AKM The authentication and key management method defined by 802.11i, and which includes 802.1x and pre-shared key.

hh3cDot11StationAssociateTable.name: hh3cDot11StationAssociateTable
hh3cDot11StationAssociateTable.description: This table contains the information of stations which are associating with the wireless network (current AC).

hh3cDot11StationAssociateEntry.name: hh3cDot11StationAssociateEntry
hh3cDot11StationAssociateEntry.description: Each entry contains association information of each station.

hh3cDot11StationMAC.name: hh3cDot11StationMAC
hh3cDot11StationMAC.description: Represents the unique MAC Address of station.

hh3cDot11StationIPAddress.name: hh3cDot11StationIPAddress
hh3cDot11StationIPAddress.description: Represents the IP address of the station.

hh3cDot11StationUserName.name: hh3cDot11StationUserName
hh3cDot11StationUserName.description: Represents the user name of the station.

hh3cDot11StationTxRateSet.name: hh3cDot11StationTxRateSet
hh3cDot11StationTxRateSet.description: Represents the current transmit data rates for this station. Each byte will represent one rate. If the MSB(Most significant bit) is set, then this rate is a mandantory rate. Otherwise, it is optional.

hh3cDot11StationUpTime.name: hh3cDot11StationUpTime
hh3cDot11StationUpTime.description: The time in seconds, how long this station has been associated with this device.

hh3cDot11StationSignalStrength.name: hh3cDot11StationSignalStrength
hh3cDot11StationSignalStrength.description: Represents a device-dependent measure of the signal strength of latest packet received from this station.

hh3cDot11StationRSSI.name: hh3cDot11StationRSSI
hh3cDot11StationRSSI.description: Represents a device-dependent measure of the RSSI. It is the received signal strength indication. The maximum value is defined by chip set vendors

hh3cDot11StationChannel.name: hh3cDot11StationChannel
hh3cDot11StationChannel.description: Represents current radio channel used by station.

hh3cDot11StationPowerSaveMode.name: hh3cDot11StationPowerSaveMode
hh3cDot11StationPowerSaveMode.description: Represents the power management mode of this station. The following values are supported: active - This station is not in power-save mode and it is actively sending or receiving data. powersave - This station is in power-save mode and it wakes up after sometime to check for buffer data.

hh3cDot11StationAid.name: hh3cDot11StationAid
hh3cDot11StationAid.description: Represents the association identification number of station.

hh3cDot11StationVlanId.name: hh3cDot11StationVlanId
hh3cDot11StationVlanId.description: Represents Vlan ID to which the station is associated.

hh3cDot11StationAuthenMode.name: hh3cDot11StationAuthenMode
hh3cDot11StationAuthenMode.description: Represents the Authentication mode defined by 802.11.

hh3cDot11StationAKMMode.name: hh3cDot11StationAKMMode
hh3cDot11StationAKMMode.description: Represents the key management mode defined by 802.11i.

hh3cDot11StationSecurityCiphers.name: hh3cDot11StationSecurityCiphers
hh3cDot11StationSecurityCiphers.description: Represents the frame encryption cipher type used by station.

hh3cDot11StationSSIDEncryptMode.name: hh3cDot11StationSSIDEncryptMode
hh3cDot11StationSSIDEncryptMode.description: Represents the encryption mode for this ESS.

hh3cDot11StationRxSNR.name: hh3cDot11StationRxSNR
hh3cDot11StationRxSNR.description: Represents the signal and noise strength ratio of frame reception.

hh3cDot11StationTxRate.name: hh3cDot11StationTxRate
hh3cDot11StationTxRate.description: Represents the transmission rate of frame.

hh3cDot11StationRxRate.name: hh3cDot11StationRxRate
hh3cDot11StationRxRate.description: Represents the reception rate of frame.

hh3cDot11StationVendorName.name: hh3cDot11StationVendorName
hh3cDot11StationVendorName.description: Represents the vendor name of the station.

hh3cDot11StationRadioMode.name: hh3cDot11StationRadioMode
hh3cDot11StationRadioMode.description: Represents which radio type supported by the station. The WLAN system support the following possible radio types. dot11a(1), dot11b(2), dot11g(4), dot11n(8) For a station,it could support only one radio type at the same time.

hh3cDot11StationRxNoise.name: hh3cDot11StationRxNoise
hh3cDot11StationRxNoise.description: Represents the received noise of the station.

hh3cDot11StationTxSpeed.name: hh3cDot11StationTxSpeed
hh3cDot11StationTxSpeed.description: Represents the bytes of transmitted data frames to the station per second in sample interval.

hh3cDot11StationRxSpeed.name: hh3cDot11StationRxSpeed
hh3cDot11StationRxSpeed.description: Represents the bytes of received data frames from the station per second in sample interval.

hh3cDot11StationWmmMode.name: hh3cDot11StationWmmMode
hh3cDot11StationWmmMode.description: Represents the QoS mode of station. The following values are supported: wmm - This QoS function is supported by this station. nonwmm - This QoS function is not supported by this station.

hh3cDot11StationSecIEStatus.name: hh3cDot11StationSecIEStatus
hh3cDot11StationSecIEStatus.description: Represents the security Information element for this station.

hh3cDot11StationUpTimeTicks.name: hh3cDot11StationUpTimeTicks
hh3cDot11StationUpTimeTicks.description: Represents how long this station has been associated with this device.

hh3cDot11StationRadioMode2.name: hh3cDot11StationRadioMode2
hh3cDot11StationRadioMode2.description: Represents which radio type supported by the station. The WLAN system support the following possible radio types. dot11a(1), dot11b(2), dot11g(4), dot11an(8), dot11gn(16) For a station,it could support only one radio type at the same time.

hh3cDot11StationAssTime.name: hh3cDot11StationAssTime
hh3cDot11StationAssTime.description: Represents the time at which the station connected.

hh3cDot11StationUserAuthType.name: hh3cDot11StationUserAuthType
hh3cDot11StationUserAuthType.description: Represents the type of user authentication with this station. portalAuth - The authentication lunched by portal pop-up program which is need input username and passward,exclude MAC authentication. authFree - There is no need others authentiaction,user will surf internet after association. associateAuth - Include WEP PSK 802.1X authentication. macAuth - MAC Authentication apply with access device, a Remote Authentication Dial-In User Service (RADIUS) server or message netgate to realize fast authentication.

hh3cDot11StationRfPingTest.name: hh3cDot11StationRfPingTest
hh3cDot11StationRfPingTest.description: This object is used to start rfping test of the station. It will return false for get operation.

hh3cDot11StationMaxRate.name: hh3cDot11StationMaxRate
hh3cDot11StationMaxRate.description: Represents the max negotiation rate of the station.

hh3cDot11StationPowerSaveModeCM.name: hh3cDot11StationPowerSaveModeCM
hh3cDot11StationPowerSaveModeCM.description: Represents the power management mode of the client. The following values are supported: active - This client is not in power-save mode and it is actively sending or receiving data. powersave - This client is in power-save mode and it wakes up after some time to check for buffer data.

hh3cDot11StationAuthenModeCM.name: hh3cDot11StationAuthenModeCM
hh3cDot11StationAuthenModeCM.description: Represents the authentication mode defined by 802.11. The following values are supported: opensystem - Do not authenticate. sharedkey - System will use challenge message to authenticate the client.

hh3cDot11StationAKMModeCM.name: hh3cDot11StationAKMModeCM
hh3cDot11StationAKMModeCM.description: Represents the key management mode defined by 802.11i. The following values are supported: none - no key management mode configured, psk - pre-shared key authentication, radius - 802.1x authentication, wlanex - wlanex.

hh3cDot11StationSecurityCiphersCM.name: hh3cDot11StationSecurityCiphersCM
hh3cDot11StationSecurityCiphersCM.description: Represents the frame encryption cipher type used by station. The following values are supported: none - clear text or no cipher method is configure, wep40 - 40-bit WEP key, wep104 - 104-bit WEP key, tkip - WPA Temporal Key encryption, aesccmp - WPA AES CCMP encryption, wpisms4 - ext encryption.

hh3cDot11StationSecIEStatusCM.name: hh3cDot11StationSecIEStatusCM
hh3cDot11StationSecIEStatusCM.description: Represents the security Information element for this station. The following values are supported: none - both wpa and wpa2 are disabled, wpa - only enable wpa, wpa2 - only enable wpa2, wlanex - only enable wlanex.

hh3cDot11StationAPRelationTable.name: hh3cDot11StationAPRelationTable
hh3cDot11StationAPRelationTable.description: This table contains relation-ship between station, AP, Radio and WLANID, and the detailed information of station is kept in the hh3cDot11StaAssociateTable table.

hh3cDot11StationAPRelationEntry.name: hh3cDot11StationAPRelationEntry
hh3cDot11StationAPRelationEntry.description: Each entry contains relation-ship information with AP, Radio and WLANID of each station.

hh3cDot11CurrAPID.name: hh3cDot11CurrAPID
hh3cDot11CurrAPID.description: To uniquely identify each AP, and relation-ship between hh3cDot11CurrAPID and AP device will be static.

hh3cDot11CurrWlanID.name: hh3cDot11CurrWlanID
hh3cDot11CurrWlanID.description: Represents WLAN ID of the BSS the station associated to.

hh3cDot11CurrAntennaID.name: hh3cDot11CurrAntennaID
hh3cDot11CurrAntennaID.description: Represents Antenna ID of the station associated to.

hh3cDot11StationStatisTable.name: hh3cDot11StationStatisTable
hh3cDot11StationStatisTable.description: This table contains statistics and status of all stations in the hh3cDot11StaAssociateTable.

hh3cDot11StationStatisEntry.name: hh3cDot11StationStatisEntry
hh3cDot11StationStatisEntry.description: This entry contains statistics and status for each station.

hh3cDot11StationRxFrameCnt.name: hh3cDot11StationRxFrameCnt
hh3cDot11StationRxFrameCnt.description: Represents the count of frames that are received by AP from station.

hh3cDot11StationTxFrameCnt.name: hh3cDot11StationTxFrameCnt
hh3cDot11StationTxFrameCnt.description: Represents the count of frames that are sent to station from AP.

hh3cDot11StationDropFrameCnt.name: hh3cDot11StationDropFrameCnt
hh3cDot11StationDropFrameCnt.description: Represents the count of frames that are dropped.

hh3cDot11StationRxFrameBytes.name: hh3cDot11StationRxFrameBytes
hh3cDot11StationRxFrameBytes.description: Represents the count of bytes that are received by AP from station.

hh3cDot11StationTxFrameBytes.name: hh3cDot11StationTxFrameBytes
hh3cDot11StationTxFrameBytes.description: Represents the count of bytes that are sent to station from AP.

hh3cDot11StationDropFrameBytes.name: hh3cDot11StationDropFrameBytes
hh3cDot11StationDropFrameBytes.description: Represents how many bytes are dropped.

hh3cDot11StationRxRetryPkts.name: hh3cDot11StationRxRetryPkts
hh3cDot11StationRxRetryPkts.description: Represents the count of frames that are retransmitted to AP from station.

hh3cDot11StationTxRetryPkts.name: hh3cDot11StationTxRetryPkts
hh3cDot11StationTxRetryPkts.description: Represents the count of frames that are retransmitted to station from AP.

hh3cDot11StationRxRetryBytes.name: hh3cDot11StationRxRetryBytes
hh3cDot11StationRxRetryBytes.description: Represents the count of bytes that are retransmitted to AP from station.

hh3cDot11StationTxRetryBytes.name: hh3cDot11StationTxRetryBytes
hh3cDot11StationTxRetryBytes.description: Represents the count of bytes that are retransmitted to station from AP.

hh3cDot11StationThroughput.name: hh3cDot11StationThroughput
hh3cDot11StationThroughput.description: Represents how many payload bytes of data frame are sent and received by station.

hh3cDot11StationSuccessTxCnt.name: hh3cDot11StationSuccessTxCnt
hh3cDot11StationSuccessTxCnt.description: Represents how many frames have been successfully sent to station.

hh3cDot11StationSuccessTxDataCnt.name: hh3cDot11StationSuccessTxDataCnt
hh3cDot11StationSuccessTxDataCnt.description: Represents how many data frames have been successfully sent to station.

hh3cDot11StationRxDataFrameCnt.name: hh3cDot11StationRxDataFrameCnt
hh3cDot11StationRxDataFrameCnt.description: Represents how many data frames have been received from station.

hh3cDot11StationTxDataFrameCnt.name: hh3cDot11StationTxDataFrameCnt
hh3cDot11StationTxDataFrameCnt.description: Represents how many data frames have been sent to station.

hh3cDot11StationRxDataFrameBytes.name: hh3cDot11StationRxDataFrameBytes
hh3cDot11StationRxDataFrameBytes.description: Represents how many bytes of data frames have been received from station.

hh3cDot11StationTxDataFrameBytes.name: hh3cDot11StationTxDataFrameBytes
hh3cDot11StationTxDataFrameBytes.description: Represents how many bytes of data frames have been sent to station.

hh3cDot11StationRxFragCnt.name: hh3cDot11StationRxFragCnt
hh3cDot11StationRxFragCnt.description: Represents the number of fragmented data frames that received from station.

hh3cDot11StaRxErrDataFrameCnt.name: hh3cDot11StaRxErrDataFrameCnt
hh3cDot11StaRxErrDataFrameCnt.description: Represents the count of error data frames that are received by AP from station.

hh3cDot11StaTxRetryDataFrameCnt.name: hh3cDot11StaTxRetryDataFrameCnt
hh3cDot11StaTxRetryDataFrameCnt.description: Represents the count of data frames that are retransmitted to station from AP.

hh3cDot11StaTxDataRatePkts.name: hh3cDot11StaTxDataRatePkts
hh3cDot11StaTxDataRatePkts.description: Represents how many data frames of each rate have been received from station.

hh3cDot11StaRxDataRatePkts.name: hh3cDot11StaRxDataRatePkts
hh3cDot11StaRxDataRatePkts.description: Represents how many data frames of each rate have been sent to station.

hh3cDot11StaTxSignalStrengthPkts.name: hh3cDot11StaTxSignalStrengthPkts
hh3cDot11StaTxSignalStrengthPkts.description: Represents how many data frames of different signal strength have been received from station.

hh3cDot11StaInternetRxFrameBytes.name: hh3cDot11StaInternetRxFrameBytes
hh3cDot11StaInternetRxFrameBytes.description: Internet traffic bytes received from station.

hh3cDot11StaInternetTxFrameBytes.name: hh3cDot11StaInternetTxFrameBytes
hh3cDot11StaInternetTxFrameBytes.description: Internet traffic bytes sent to station.

hh3cDot11StaLocalRxFrameBytes.name: hh3cDot11StaLocalRxFrameBytes
hh3cDot11StaLocalRxFrameBytes.description: Local traffic bytes received from station.

hh3cDot11StaLocalTxFrameBytes.name: hh3cDot11StaLocalTxFrameBytes
hh3cDot11StaLocalTxFrameBytes.description: Local traffic bytes sent to station.

hh3cDot11StationRfPingTable.name: hh3cDot11StationRfPingTable
hh3cDot11StationRfPingTable.description: This table contains statistics of all stations in the hh3cDot11StationRfPingTable.

hh3cDot11StationRfPingEntry.name: hh3cDot11StationRfPingEntry
hh3cDot11StationRfPingEntry.description: This entry contains statistics for each station's RfPing results.

hh3cDot11StationRfPingIndex.name: hh3cDot11StationRfPingIndex
hh3cDot11StationRfPingIndex.description: Represents the rate index for the station.

hh3cDot11StationRfPingRate.name: hh3cDot11StationRfPingRate
hh3cDot11StationRfPingRate.description: Represents the rate at which the radio interface sends wireless ping frames.

hh3cDot11StationRfPingTxCnt.name: hh3cDot11StationRfPingTxCnt
hh3cDot11StationRfPingTxCnt.description: Represents the number of wireless ping frames that the radio interface sent.

hh3cDot11StationRfPingRxCnt.name: hh3cDot11StationRfPingRxCnt
hh3cDot11StationRfPingRxCnt.description: Represents the number of wireless ping frames that the radio interface received from the client.

hh3cDot11StationRfPingRssi.name: hh3cDot11StationRfPingRssi
hh3cDot11StationRfPingRssi.description: Represents the client signal strength detected by the AP.

hh3cDot11StationRfPingRetries.name: hh3cDot11StationRfPingRetries
hh3cDot11StationRfPingRetries.description: Represents the total number of retransmitted ping frames.

hh3cDot11StationRfPingRtt.name: hh3cDot11StationRfPingRtt
hh3cDot11StationRfPingRtt.description: Round-trip time (RTT) from the time when the radio interface send a ping packet to the time when it receives a response from the client.

hh3cDot11StationMICErrorTrap.name: hh3cDot11StationMICErrorTrap
hh3cDot11StationMICErrorTrap.description: This notification is to indicate the occurrence of a MIC failure in a certain station.

hh3cDot11StationAuthenErrorTrap.name: hh3cDot11StationAuthenErrorTrap
hh3cDot11StationAuthenErrorTrap.description: This notification is to indicate which station happened authentication failure.

hh3cDot11StationAuthorFailTrap.name: hh3cDot11StationAuthorFailTrap
hh3cDot11StationAuthorFailTrap.description: This trap is sent if a station authorization fails.

hh3cDot11StationAssocFailTrap.name: hh3cDot11StationAssocFailTrap
hh3cDot11StationAssocFailTrap.description: This trap is sent if a station association fails.

hh3cDot11StationDeAssocTrap.name: hh3cDot11StationDeAssocTrap
hh3cDot11StationDeAssocTrap.description: This trap is sent if a station de-association occurred.

hh3cDot11StationAuthorSuccTrap.name: hh3cDot11StationAuthorSuccTrap
hh3cDot11StationAuthorSuccTrap.description: This trap is sent when a station is authorized successfully.

hh3cDot11StationRoamingTrap.name: hh3cDot11StationRoamingTrap
hh3cDot11StationRoamingTrap.description: This trap is sent when a station roamed successfully.

hh3cDot11StationDisconnectTrap.name: hh3cDot11StationDisconnectTrap
hh3cDot11StationDisconnectTrap.description: This notification is sent when station disconnects with AP.

hh3cDot11UserDisconnectTrap.name: hh3cDot11UserDisconnectTrap
hh3cDot11UserDisconnectTrap.description: This notification is sent when user disconnects with AP.

hh3cDot11StationTrapBSSID.name: hh3cDot11StationTrapBSSID
hh3cDot11StationTrapBSSID.description: Represents on which BSSID of AP the event happened.

hh3cDot11StationTrapStaMAC.name: hh3cDot11StationTrapStaMAC
hh3cDot11StationTrapStaMAC.description: Represents the MAC address of station which happened message integrity check (MIC) errors.

hh3cDot11StationSessionStartTime.name: hh3cDot11StationSessionStartTime
hh3cDot11StationSessionStartTime.description: Represents the time at which the station connected.

hh3cDot11StationAssocFailCause.name: hh3cDot11StationAssocFailCause
hh3cDot11StationAssocFailCause.description: Represents the cause of the station association failure.

hh3cDot11StationAuthorFailCause.name: hh3cDot11StationAuthorFailCause
hh3cDot11StationAuthorFailCause.description: Represents the cause of the station authorization failure.

hh3cDot11StationFailCauseDesc.name: hh3cDot11StationFailCauseDesc
hh3cDot11StationFailCauseDesc.description: Represents the failure description of the station.

hh3cDot11StationSessionDuration.name: hh3cDot11StationSessionDuration
hh3cDot11StationSessionDuration.description: Represents the duration of the station sesssion.

hh3cDot11StationRoamingTime.name: hh3cDot11StationRoamingTime
hh3cDot11StationRoamingTime.description: Represents the time at which the station roamed.

hh3cDot11StationACIPAddress.name: hh3cDot11StationACIPAddress
hh3cDot11StationACIPAddress.description: For roam-in station, it represents the ip address of home AC. For roam-out station, it represents the ip address of foreign AC.

hh3cDot11StationAPName.name: hh3cDot11StationAPName
hh3cDot11StationAPName.description: Name of the AP which the station connects to.

hh3cDot11StationBSSID.name: hh3cDot11StationBSSID
hh3cDot11StationBSSID.description: BSSID which the station connects to.

hh3cDot11StaDisconnectReason.name: hh3cDot11StaDisconnectReason
hh3cDot11StaDisconnectReason.description: Reason why the station disconnects with the AP.

hh3cDot11StationACIPv6Add.name: hh3cDot11StationACIPv6Add
hh3cDot11StationACIPv6Add.description: For roam-in station, it represents the IPv6 address of home AC. For roam-out station, it represents the IPv6 address of foreign AC.

hh3cDot11StationTrapAPMacAddress.name: hh3cDot11StationTrapAPMacAddress
hh3cDot11StationTrapAPMacAddress.description: Represents the MAC address of an AP.
